1177
00:55:53,349 --> 00:55:55,953
And it was like trying
to find work at midnight

1178
00:55:55,954 --> 00:55:58,141
In a thick fog among strangers.

1179
00:55:58,142 --> 00:56:00,954
Hence I started at the bottom,

1180
00:56:00,955 --> 00:56:02,934
Like any newcomer,

1181
00:56:02,935 --> 00:56:05,853
For as little
as $1,000 a script.

1182
00:56:05,854 --> 00:56:08,457
In the first 18 months

1183
00:56:08,458 --> 00:56:10,855
I wrote 12 scripts...

1184
00:56:10,856 --> 00:56:15,753
Which normally would take
between four and six
years to do.

1185
00:56:15,754 --> 00:56:18,671
The necessity of keeping
the money grinding in

1186
00:56:18,672 --> 00:56:21,276
Made it impossible for me
to take as much as a month off

1187
00:56:21,277 --> 00:56:23,674
And gamble on an original
which might sell for enough

1188
00:56:23,675 --> 00:56:27,216
To give me more gambling room.

1189
00:56:27,217 --> 00:56:32,010
Also, I am overly timid
and evasive

1190
00:56:32,011 --> 00:56:34,511
When I owe money

1191
00:56:34,512 --> 00:56:37,951
And I can't see
just how I'm going to
pay it back.

1192
00:56:40,453 --> 00:56:44,307
This letter, then,
is an apology

1193
00:56:44,308 --> 00:56:47,435
Which I hope you will be
generous enough to accept.

1194
00:56:49,520 --> 00:56:52,749
I enclose a check for $50,

1195
00:56:52,750 --> 00:56:55,147
Which I shall now be able
to repeat every month

1196
00:56:55,148 --> 00:56:58,272
Until the money
you so very graciously
lent me

1197
00:56:58,273 --> 00:57:00,879
Is paid off in full."

1198
00:57:08,799 --> 00:57:11,091
One of the objects
of a blacklist

1199
00:57:11,092 --> 00:57:13,905
Is to deprive the victim

1200
00:57:13,906 --> 00:57:16,405
Of economic security

1201
00:57:16,407 --> 00:57:19,949
And to drastically lower
his living standards

1202
00:57:19,950 --> 00:57:22,034
To the point
where he will yield.

1203
00:57:22,035 --> 00:57:24,847
Well, that being
their objective,

1204
00:57:24,848 --> 00:57:28,599
My objective is to maintain
those living standards
in spite of it.

1205
00:57:28,600 --> 00:57:32,664
Trumbo began to work
very very hard
and very fast.

1206
00:57:32,665 --> 00:57:35,268
<i>And he would have</i>
<i>three stories</i>
<i>going at once</i>

1207
00:57:35,269 --> 00:57:37,354
<i>Because he was beginning</i>
<i>to have to sell stuff</i>

1208
00:57:37,355 --> 00:57:39,854
<i>Under other names</i>
<i>or with a front.</i>

1209
00:57:39,855 --> 00:57:41,730
So there were a lot of secrets.

1210
00:57:41,731 --> 00:57:44,232
He had many, you know,
different names.

1211
00:57:44,233 --> 00:57:47,045
And the phone would ring

1212
00:57:47,046 --> 00:57:49,025
And it was never
the wrong number

1213
00:57:49,026 --> 00:57:51,215
As far as I was concerned.
I'd always just
call my dad.

1214
00:57:51,111 --> 00:57:53,299
Trumbo:
<i>I had 13 pseudonyms,</i>
<i>all told.</i>

1215
00:57:53,300 --> 00:57:56,112
<i>I had Irish names.</i>
<i>I had Jewish names.</i>

1216
00:57:56,113 --> 00:57:58,508
<i>I had Anglo-Saxon names.</i>

1217
00:57:58,509 --> 00:58:01,010
<i>Give them their preference.</i>

1218
00:58:01,011 --> 00:58:03,617
<i>So you say</i>
<i>Sam Jackson calling</i>
<i>or Doc Abbott</i>

1219
00:58:03,618 --> 00:58:06,637
<i>Or Theodore Flaxman</i>
<i>or Evelyn Dumain.</i>

1220
00:58:06,638 --> 00:58:08,098
My dad...
his best friend,

1221
00:58:08,099 --> 00:58:10,807
One of the members
of this group, was Ian hunter.

1222
00:58:10,808 --> 00:58:12,787
And Ian had an academy award.

1223
00:58:12,788 --> 00:58:16,121
Ian's was for this
beautiful movie called
"Roman holiday."

1224
00:58:16,122 --> 00:58:19,873
<i>It wasn't until I was</i>
<i>in my early 30s</i>

1225
00:58:19,874 --> 00:58:24,249
<i>That I learned</i>
<i>that Ian had not written</i>
<i>"Roman holiday."</i>

1226
00:58:24,250 --> 00:58:27,376
<i>Trumbo had written</i>
<i>the original story.</i>

1227
00:58:27,377 --> 00:58:29,877
<i>Ian had fronted for Trumbo.</i>

1228
00:58:29,878 --> 00:58:33,004
<i>Ian hadn't been</i>
<i>blacklisted yet.</i>

1229
00:58:33,005 --> 00:58:36,026
And when the credits
were redistributed

1230
00:58:36,027 --> 00:58:38,840
Sometime in the '90s to Trumbo

1231
00:58:38,841 --> 00:58:41,447
<i>The whole experience</i>
<i>was embarrassing.</i>

1232
00:58:41,448 --> 00:58:45,198
<i>Just the blacklist</i>
<i>is a little bit more</i>
<i>complicated.</i>

1233
00:58:45,199 --> 00:58:48,531
It just has these
repercussions.

1234
00:58:48,533 --> 00:58:51,451
I thought a little wine
might be good.

1235
00:58:53,536 --> 00:58:55,097
Shall I cook something?

1236
00:58:55,098 --> 00:58:57,077
No kitchen.

1237
00:58:57,079 --> 00:58:59,372
Nothing to cook.
I always eat out.

1238
00:58:59,373 --> 00:59:00,933
Do you like that?

1239
00:59:00,934 --> 00:59:03,540
I like this knowledge
what one likes.

1240
00:59:03,541 --> 00:59:06,250
Is it...?

1241
00:59:07,500 --> 00:59:10,522
No, it isn't.

1242
00:59:13,336 --> 00:59:15,940
Ray Murphy was a young man

1243
00:59:15,941 --> 00:59:18,338
My father met
in the south pacific.

1244
00:59:18,339 --> 00:59:20,839
<i>Ray later became</i>
<i>a front for my father.</i>

1245
00:59:20,840 --> 00:59:23,548
<i>And we needed</i>
<i>the money as usual</i>

1246
00:59:23,549 --> 00:59:25,840
When the script sold.

1247
00:59:25,842 --> 00:59:28,551
And my father was expecting it

1248
00:59:28,552 --> 00:59:30,531
And it wasn't coming.

1249
00:59:30,532 --> 00:59:32,198
So he made inquiries

1250
00:59:32,199 --> 00:59:34,491
And a few weeks later
discovered

1251
00:59:34,492 --> 00:59:37,617
<i>That Ray Murphy</i>
<i>had died suddenly.</i>

1252
00:59:37,618 --> 00:59:41,369
"dear Mrs. Murphy,

1253
00:59:41,370 --> 00:59:44,495
I want to tell you
about your son

1254
00:59:44,496 --> 00:59:47,205
And my relationship with him,

1255
00:59:47,206 --> 00:59:50,435
And of my wife's sorrow
and my own

1256
00:59:50,436 --> 00:59:52,521
That he is no longer living.

1257
00:59:52,522 --> 00:59:56,375
It has been
my privilege, since 1945,

1258
00:59:56,376 --> 00:59:58,252
To be Ray's friend.

1259
00:59:58,253 --> 01:00:01,691
It came about
in the following manner:

1260
01:00:01,692 --> 01:00:04,609
In June of 1945

1261
01:00:04,610 --> 01:00:07,216
A party of six or seven
war correspondents

1262
01:00:07,217 --> 01:00:10,132
Embarked from
San Francisco by air

1263
01:00:10,133 --> 01:00:14,197
On a three-month tour
of pacific battle areas.

1264
01:00:14,198 --> 01:00:17,636
<i>Among the correspondents</i>
<i>were Ray and I.</i>

1265
01:00:17,637 --> 01:00:19,721
<i>During the invasion</i> <i>of Borneo,</i>

1266
01:00:19,617 --> 01:00:21,284
<i>Ray and I went ashore</i>
<i>in a landing craft</i>

1267
01:00:21,180 --> 01:00:23,577
<i>Between the first</i>
<i>and second waves,</i>

1268
01:00:23,578 --> 01:00:25,348
Dodging mortar fire

1269
01:00:25,349 --> 01:00:27,640
As we sprinted across the sand.

1270
01:00:27,641 --> 01:00:31,184
From a slit trench outside
the governor's palace

1271
01:00:31,185 --> 01:00:33,684
Ray and I spotted a hilltop

1272
01:00:33,685 --> 01:00:36,290
Which we believed
would give us a better view

1273
01:00:36,291 --> 01:00:39,312
Of what was going on,
and decided to climb it.

1274
01:00:39,313 --> 01:00:41,606
When we finally reached
the top of the hill

1275
01:00:41,607 --> 01:00:44,002
We found an abandoned AA Gun

1276
01:00:44,003 --> 01:00:46,504
That had been knocked out
by naval fire,

1277
01:00:46,505 --> 01:00:49,526
And no sign of a human being.

1278
01:00:49,527 --> 01:00:51,609
We took what cover we could

1279
01:00:51,610 --> 01:00:54,008
When we heard sounds
of approaching troops,

1280
01:00:54,009 --> 01:00:56,821
Thinking the Japanese
were returning.

1281
01:00:56,822 --> 01:01:00,364
Moments later a grim-looking
Australian assault group

1282
01:01:00,365 --> 01:01:02,448
With fixed bayonets appeared

1283
01:01:02,449 --> 01:01:05,262
Expecting to meet the enemy.

1284
01:01:05,263 --> 01:01:08,180
Well in advance
of our armed forces,

1285
01:01:08,181 --> 01:01:10,160
As it turned out,

1286
01:01:10,161 --> 01:01:15,371
Ray and I had accidentally
captured the hill.

1287
01:01:15,372 --> 01:01:17,977
<i>On the fourth day</i>
<i>of the campaign,</i>

1288
01:01:17,978 --> 01:01:20,687
<i>The outcome being</i> <i>beyond doubt,</i>

1289
01:01:20,688 --> 01:01:23,708
<i>Our group decided</i>
<i>to return to Tawi Tawi.</i>

1290
01:01:23,709 --> 01:01:26,626
Once off we retired
into the main cabin.

1291
01:01:26,627 --> 01:01:30,795
Somewhere off Japanese
occupied celebes,

1292
01:01:30,796 --> 01:01:33,400
The alarm signifying
an air attack

1293
01:01:33,401 --> 01:01:35,588
Went off in the cabin.

1294
01:01:35,589 --> 01:01:37,985
It could only mean that a zero

1295
01:01:37,987 --> 01:01:40,592
Had risen from celebes
and was attacking.

1296
01:01:40,593 --> 01:01:43,613
I was on the top bunk.
I looked down.

1297
01:01:43,614 --> 01:01:46,948
Ray was lying full length
on the floor

1298
01:01:46,949 --> 01:01:49,657
Between two other men,
his helmet on.

1299
01:01:49,659 --> 01:01:52,159
He looked up at me

1300
01:01:52,160 --> 01:01:54,451
And although his face was,
I daresay,

1301
01:01:54,452 --> 01:01:56,640
As pale as my own, he smiled.

1302
01:01:56,641 --> 01:01:58,620
Then he said,

1303
01:01:58,621 --> 01:02:02,684
'goodbye, Trumbo.'

1304
01:02:02,685 --> 01:02:04,769
I cannot quite describe

1305
01:02:04,770 --> 01:02:07,270
My emotions at that moment.

1306
01:02:07,271 --> 01:02:10,814
Perhaps I thought of
my own son, then only four;

1307
01:02:10,815 --> 01:02:13,939
Perhaps I thought
of my father long dead;

1308
01:02:13,941 --> 01:02:18,733
I certainly felt that a son
not my son

1309
01:02:18,734 --> 01:02:22,069
Had chosen me
from among that company

1310
01:02:22,070 --> 01:02:26,028
As the one he wished
to say goodbye to,

1311
01:02:26,029 --> 01:02:28,426
And that a father
not his father

1312
01:02:28,427 --> 01:02:30,615
Had responded.

1313
01:02:30,616 --> 01:02:33,532
The fact,
as it later turned out,

1314
01:02:33,533 --> 01:02:37,388
That there was no zero
within a hundred Miles
and no danger.

1315
01:02:37,389 --> 01:02:40,619
That the whole incident
was a ludicrous mistake
of nerves

1316
01:02:40,620 --> 01:02:42,808
On the part of the crew

1317
01:02:42,809 --> 01:02:45,413
In no way diminishes
my memory of that moment,

1318
01:02:45,414 --> 01:02:50,624
Nor the surge of love
I felt for your son.

1319
01:02:52,188 --> 01:02:57,084
We managed to correspond
intermittently ever since.

1320
01:02:57,086 --> 01:02:59,065
Ray went to India,

1321
01:02:59,066 --> 01:03:01,774
And later published
his first novel;

1322
01:03:01,775 --> 01:03:06,256
I went before
the house committee
on un-American activities

1323
01:03:06,257 --> 01:03:09,486
And later
served my first term
in a penitentiary.

1324
01:03:09,487 --> 01:03:11,572
I was at that time,
as I am now,

1325
01:03:11,573 --> 01:03:15,635
Blacklisted
by motion pictures,
publishers, and magazines.

1326
01:03:15,636 --> 01:03:18,242
It was typical
of his generous nature

1327
01:03:18,243 --> 01:03:21,992
That he offered
to collaborate with me
for motion pictures,

1328
01:03:21,993 --> 01:03:24,077
And to put his name alone

1329
01:03:24,078 --> 01:03:26,994
To the product of our
mutual endeavors.

1330
01:03:26,995 --> 01:03:31,372
It was typical of my need
that I accepted.

1331
01:03:31,373 --> 01:03:33,664
During our last visits,

1332
01:03:33,665 --> 01:03:36,582
<i>In a moment</i>
<i>of temporary depression</i>

1333
01:03:36,583 --> 01:03:39,500
<i>Common to young men</i>
<i>who are both sensitive</i>

1334
01:03:39,501 --> 01:03:42,002
And intelligent
beyond their years,

1335
01:03:42,004 --> 01:03:43,982
Ray told me

1336
01:03:43,983 --> 01:03:46,691
That he thought
he believed in nothing;

1337
01:03:46,692 --> 01:03:49,818
He felt himself
a complete cynic.

1338
01:03:49,819 --> 01:03:52,840
It was, of course, not true.

1339
01:03:52,841 --> 01:03:55,550
A day or two later

1340
01:03:55,551 --> 01:03:57,426
When he brought a copy
of my novel

1341
01:03:57,427 --> 01:04:00,032
'Johnny got his gun'
for me to inscribe,

1342
01:04:00,033 --> 01:04:02,532
I wrote in it
what I really felt

1343
01:04:02,533 --> 01:04:06,492
About him and his future.

1344
01:04:06,493 --> 01:04:10,660
He telephoned me
the next day to thank me.

1345
01:04:10,661 --> 01:04:13,891
He said, 'I hope
I can live up to it.'

1346
01:04:13,892 --> 01:04:15,975
I should have told him then,

1347
01:04:15,976 --> 01:04:18,372
And now have only you to tell

1348
01:04:18,373 --> 01:04:21,292
That he already had."

1349
01:04:25,564 --> 01:04:27,649
Man:
<i>Prisoner, show yourself.</i>

1350
01:04:33,693 --> 01:04:37,340
( coughing )

1351
01:04:37,341 --> 01:04:39,946
Give me the name
and you're back
on full rations.

1352
01:04:41,196 --> 01:04:44,947
Just one name.

1353
01:04:44,949 --> 01:04:47,658
I was born skinny.

1354
01:04:50,889 --> 01:04:52,765
Then you'll die.

1355
01:04:55,995 --> 01:04:58,496
Christopher Trumbo:
<i>In 1957 or '58</i>

1356
01:04:58,497 --> 01:05:02,039
<i>The situation</i>
<i>in Hollywood in terms of</i>
<i>blacklisted writers is</i>

1357
01:05:02,040 --> 01:05:04,437
Unless you cooperate
with the committee,

1358
01:05:04,438 --> 01:05:07,458
Unless you, you know,
do what it asks you to,

1359
01:05:07,459 --> 01:05:09,125
You won't be employed.

1360
01:05:09,126 --> 01:05:12,668
Navasky:
<i>The next generation</i>
<i>of witnesses</i>

1361
01:05:12,669 --> 01:05:15,274
<i>Faced a different</i>
<i>sort of choice.</i>

1362
01:05:15,275 --> 01:05:17,777
<i>They could take the first</i>
<i>amendment like the 10</i>

1363
01:05:17,778 --> 01:05:20,485
<i>And then their assumption was</i>
<i>they'd go to prison;</i>

1364
01:05:20,486 --> 01:05:22,883
<i>They could take</i>
<i>the fifth amendment</i>

1365
01:05:22,779 --> 01:05:24,341
<i>Which would keep them</i>
<i>out of prison,</i>

1366
01:05:24,237 --> 01:05:26,009
<i>But they would then</i>
<i>be blacklisted;</i>

1367
01:05:26,010 --> 01:05:28,822
<i>Or they could cooperate</i>
<i>with the committee.</i>

1368
01:05:28,823 --> 01:05:32,052
If they did that and admitted

1369
01:05:32,053 --> 01:05:34,034
That they had been members
of the communist party,

1370
01:05:34,035 --> 01:05:36,639
The next question was, "and who
else was a member with you?"

1371
01:05:36,640 --> 01:05:38,931
<i>Larry parks was</i>
<i>the first witness</i>

1372
01:05:38,932 --> 01:05:41,121
In the new round
of witnesses in 1951,

1373
01:05:41,122 --> 01:05:44,350
And parks was ready
to talk about himself.

1374
01:05:44,351 --> 01:05:47,164
He was ready to talk about
why he joined the party,

1375
01:05:47,165 --> 01:05:50,498
Which he said was
because it was the most
liberal thing around

1376
01:05:50,499 --> 01:05:52,376
And then he got out.
And he said,

1377
01:05:52,377 --> 01:05:55,709
"but don't make me name names.
Don't make me play
the informer."

1378
01:05:55,710 --> 01:05:58,003
<i>Don't present me</i>
<i>with the choice</i>

1379
01:05:58,004 --> 01:06:00,713
<i>Of either being in contempt</i>
<i>to this committee</i>

1380
01:06:00,714 --> 01:06:02,796
<i>And going to jail</i>

1381
01:06:02,797 --> 01:06:04,880
<i>Or forcing me</i>

1382
01:06:04,881 --> 01:06:06,966
<i>To crawl through the mud</i>
<i>to be an informer.</i>

1383
01:06:06,967 --> 01:06:08,840
<i>I beg you</i>

1384
01:06:08,841 --> 01:06:11,342
<i>Not to force me</i>
<i>to do this."</i>

1385
01:06:11,343 --> 01:06:13,219
Navasky:
<i>They insisted</i>
<i>that he name names</i>

1386
01:06:13,220 --> 01:06:15,928
And from then on
you had to name names

1387
01:06:15,929 --> 01:06:18,741
In order to get cleared
by the committee.

1388
01:06:18,742 --> 01:06:21,346
It is only a matter of time.

1389
01:06:21,347 --> 01:06:23,118
You think so?

1390
01:06:23,119 --> 01:06:25,828
He's on half rations now.
You can't exist on that.

1391
01:06:25,829 --> 01:06:29,579
Forced to choose between
starvation and telling,

1392
01:06:29,580 --> 01:06:32,081
What would <i>you</i> do?

1393
01:06:32,082 --> 01:06:34,894
We're not talking about me.
What would <i>you</i> do?

1394
01:06:34,895 --> 01:06:37,292
I looked hard at Dalton
and I thought,

1395
01:06:37,294 --> 01:06:40,417
What is it about this Guy
that would not...

1396
01:06:40,418 --> 01:06:43,232
Which would make him say,
"no, I'm not giving names."

1397
01:06:43,233 --> 01:06:48,130
<i>And that was</i>
<i>a psychic death kind of.</i>

1398
01:06:48,131 --> 01:06:51,256
Because you just
lost everything.

1399
01:06:51,257 --> 01:06:54,487
You were never to work again.
You were never to have
any money.

1400
01:06:54,488 --> 01:06:56,571
You went to jail.

1401
01:06:56,572 --> 01:06:58,863
I remember doing an interview

1402
01:06:58,864 --> 01:07:00,635
<i>With Adrian Scott</i>

1403
01:07:00,636 --> 01:07:02,721
<i>Who was one of</i>
<i>the Hollywood 10.</i>

1404
01:07:02,722 --> 01:07:05,117
<i>I visited him</i> <i>in his home</i>

1405
01:07:05,118 --> 01:07:08,452
<i>And all of the furniture</i>
<i>was gone.</i>

